see it :-)","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=david.pan","name":"david.pan","emailAddress":"pan_xiaolei at sina dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"david.pan","active":true},"created":"2010-01-22T02:56:02.350+0000","updated":"2010-01-22T02:56:02.350+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12446281/comment/12805742","id":"12805742","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jaakko","name":"jaakko","emailAddress":"rosvopaallikko at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jaakko Laine","active":true},"body":"Yeah, you're right. I'll have a look at this.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jaakko","name":"jaakko","emailAddress":"rosvopaallikko at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jaakko Laine","active":true},"created":"2010-01-28T01:41:18.285+0000","updated":"2010-01-28T01:41:18.285+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12446281/comment/12831379","id":"12831379","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jaakko","name":"jaakko","emailAddress":"rosvopaallikko at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jaakko Laine","active":true},"body":"This assert might fail for the reason David said, but it might also fail because targets includes a node with pending ranges that has died (for instance did not complete bootstrap). \r\n\r\nIt does not matter if a node is in pending ranges and normal token map simultaneously, as that time is very short and may only result in a write going to too many nodes once in a while. Gossip propagation is far from being instant, so writes go to wrong places routinely anyway when nodes move. It's a much smaller thing than locking whole metadata for the duration of calculations. \r\n\r\nI think removing the assert is enough. It should be removed in any case, since it is checking a condition that is no longer valid. I don't see any other problem in this part.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jaakko","name":"jaakko","emailAddress":"rosvopaallikko at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jaakko Laine","active":true},"created":"2010-02-09T09:31:36.749+0000","updated":"2010-02-09T09:31:36.749+0000"},{"self":"https://